Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.36,0:02:56.30,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(200,0)\blur1\c&H271706&\3c&HC69A75&\frz10\pos(18,960)}Nishimura's fleet
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.94,0:02:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll be feinting the enemy camp on their own. {no clue, doesnt say who or what, maybe the enemy will raid them naked, doesn't make sense to do that for a decoy fleet without teeth so maybe he means "they'll pretend to ..."; in reality, again, this is a decoy fleet so they're not supposed to raid anyone at all, only draw the enemy away from the taffy 3 guading the Leyte landings}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.48,0:03:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,In this time of extreme emergency, \Nthe only possible course of action for our 1st Air Fleet
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.63,0:03:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,is to teach our pilots a new strategy\Nof strapping 250 kg bombs to their Zeros
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.35,0:03:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and trying their utmost to sink one warship each \Nby ramming into them in a suicide attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.80,0:03:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I would like to hear your opinions on that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.89,0:03:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I cannot approve of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.39,0:03:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And the rationale is?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.91,0:03:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,During the Russo-Japanese War, even the hands on the sacrificial ships that went to blockade Port Arthur were ordered to return. {gonna be honest, I have no idea what event he's referring to; not sure what word to choose for kesshitai/決死隊 - means "a unit that went on a risky/desperate/crazy mission/prepared to death" but gotta avoid the words "suicide squad" since he's advocating for the opposite and for other reason later}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.06,0:03:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,In the current conflict as well - the midget submarines \Nin the attack on Hawaii and Pearl Harbor.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.01,0:03:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The pilots knew they'd return home \Nif the surprise attack succeeded.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.18,0:03:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why both Admiral Togo and Commander-in-Chief Yamamoto approved the execution of those plans. {assuming he means https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/T%C5%8Dg%C5%8D_Heihachir%C5%8D#Russo-Japanese_War_(1904%E2%80%931905)}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.01,0:03:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, the history of warfare of the world knows examples \Nof desperate missions, but none of them were pure suicide. {lit: there are records of kesshitai in ... but no precedent of hisshitai - kesshitai I explained before, means "prepared to die squad" but hisshitai means "certain to die squad" so an actual suicide squad... man, this is so hard to put into english}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.01,0:03:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter how poorly the war is going,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.61,0:04:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,a suicide corps that turns its men into flying bombs
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.74,0:04:07.01,Default,,0,0,0,,stands in defiance of the last 70 years \Nof Japanese naval tradition. {actually "will leave a permanent stain on" but I think this sounds cooler}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.01,0:04:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just as you said. This is a heresy \Nthat disregards all rules of military conduct.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.52,0:04:12.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.28,0:04:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The prospect of victory is no longer feasible, \Nso why don't we at least deal the biggest blow we can?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.35,0:04:23.79,Default,,0,0,0,,If we frustrate the enemy's fighting spirit, \Nthey would be willing to conclude the war sooner. {lit: "we'll create a chance; start; cue; excuse; motive; impetus; occasion to end the war" - I think he means they'll be open to negotiations about a conditional surrender}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.32,0:04:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,If we don't cut it short here...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.77,0:04:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,If we don't conclude the war, our homeland of Japan will be reduced to ashes and the nation will be no more. {lit: people; race; nation; ethnic group; ethnos of japan will go to ruin; to go under; to fall; to be destroyed; to die out; to become extinct; to perish - was "people would perish" in HA which works too}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.58,0:04:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,This is no longer about the strategy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.76,0:04:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a prayer for the people who yearn for peace. \NA vow to save them. {not sure if it's the pilots who are praying for ... or the kamikaze program is the embodiment of the people's prayer, higan as well could refer to both - can mean both "one's dearest wish" and "Buddha's vow to save humanity"}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.63,0:04:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Even knowing they'll remember me as a wicked and inhuman commander in 100 years, I'd still give that order.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.40,0:04:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because I believe \Nthat we have no other way to save Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.00,0:04:59.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir. I will also follow your lead and act upon it. {apparently men could use watashi too back in the day}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.62,0:05:09.10,Sign,,0,0,250,,{\fade(0,400)\bord0\blur1\b1\c&HD3CDCB&\pos(720,304)}Episode 17\N{\fs100}Birth of the Kamikaze Corps
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.06,0:05:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Fighter crews, gather in briefing room #1! {actually "commander's/commander officer's room" w/e that means}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.78,0:05:40.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Attention!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.01,0:05:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The fighter corps is ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.01,0:05:51.29,Default,,0,0,0,,We've received an order to form a special attack corps.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.79,0:06:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The special attack corps will specialize in suicide attacks,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.54,0:06:04.99,Default,,0,0,0,,where they strap 250 kg bombs to their Zeros \Nand ram the enemy ships.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.62,0:06:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I will hand out this paper now. \NThose who wish to volunteer, write your name on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.09,0:06:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who don't, leave it blank.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.12,0:06:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Put it in the envelope \Nand have your officer hand it directly to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.20,0:06:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,NCOs submit your paper to your superior. {no clue what he means or why, lit: noncom.off submit at hand to fulltime.off - either the mobilized off. are supposed to hand them to fulltimers - doesn't make much sense, why make exception for them? or could be that it's the continuation of previous line: hand the paper directly to your officer, those will pass it up the line - to noncom, then fulltime etc; look next line too}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.82,0:06:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,This way, nobody but me \Nwould know if you volunteered or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.38,0:06:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,If due to health concerns, \Nfamily circumstances, or any other reason,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.51,0:06:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't volunteer, \Ndon't worry about it one bit!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.47,0:06:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Submit it after careful consideration.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.12,0:06:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,May I remind you, \Nthis corps becomes active starting tomorrow. {lit: saying it just in case, this attack is implemented ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.20,0:06:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, what will you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.44,0:06:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.01,0:06:48.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The valiant taste death but once, they say. \NNo time to do it like now. {proverb: if you die once, you can't die again - means "you can only die once so choose well how to die"; russian also has it as двум смертям не бывать, а одной не миновать, but sadly, I don't think english does so I played around that famous "A coward dies a thousand times before his death" quote}{second part actually means something like "doing it sooner means less bother for everyone else [as opposed to dying infirm and in bed]"}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.78,0:06:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,300)}They say, the fool is cured only in death. \NMight as well go out with a bang! {another proverb: only death can cure stupidity - again, we have "горбатого могила исправит" but in english, only "once a fool, always a fool"}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.80,0:08:09.43,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord4\c&H161A17&\3c&HB8B5B5&}Navy Lieutenant Seki Yukio {海軍大尉関行男 - later his name is seki which is 関 and not 南 but w/e; 大尉 depending on the branch can be "captain (Army, US Marine Corps, USAF); lieutenant (Navy); flight lieutenant (RAF, RAAF, RNZAF, etc.)​" - assuming navy here bc he's clearly not from RAF or land army; https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yukio_Seki}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.74,0:08:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Lieutenant Seki, can we talk? \NThis is First Lieutenant Kuno. {this chuui doesn't depend on branch and is "first lieutenant; lieutenant junior grade​"}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.88,0:08:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.23,0:08:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I brought something special from my reserves. {https://jisho.org/word/%E5%8F%96%E3%81%A3%E3%81%A6%E3%81%8A%E3%81%8D}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.83,0:08:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,How does that sound? {lit: will we drink a cup}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.73,0:08:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? This is quite a luxurious item. \NWhere did you manage to find it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.23,0:08:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,A present from my classmate \Nwho brought it from Singapore.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.24,0:08:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.75,0:08:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's pray for each other's luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.33,0:08:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So the judgment day is finally here. {no clue what he means: 'expected to arrive (occur) in the near future'​ time came; probably means "the time to decide your fate" or something; was "the time to come clean" in ha}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.50,0:08:46.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Lieutenant Seki.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.44,0:08:49.97,Default,,0,0,0,,May I tell you how I truly feel about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.97,0:08:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.46,0:08:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't subscribe to those ramming attacks. {/don't approve of}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.11,0:08:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.72,0:09:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Vice Admiral Onishi probably approved these ramming attacks believing we'd only ever use this tactic once.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.10,0:09:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,But I know - once this tactic is introduced, \Nthere will be no stopping it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.71,0:09:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll spread to all the other Navy Air Corps as well. {plural of corps is also corps it seems}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.26,0:09:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I fear that as a result, \Neven if it started as a volunteer system,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.18,0:09:19.95,Default,,0,0,0,,it will eventually become a strategy \Nthat everyone would be coerced into.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.61,0:09:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a grain of reason to what you say.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.39,0:09:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,But if we want to prevent them... No.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.23,0:09:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Supposing we put the ramming attacks
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.27,0:09:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,on halt for now, do you have any other good plan \Nfor extricating our country from this state of the war?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.30,0:09:37.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Kuno, you actually value your life, don't you? {ns what he means: https://jisho.org/word/%E6%83%9C%E3%81%97%E3%81%84 ; was "You really will miss your life." in ha}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.29,0:09:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Lieutenant Seki...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.84,0:09:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't want to die either, \Nup until about 10 minutes ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.26,0:09:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But now I made up my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.00,0:09:54.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I would like to volunteer for the special attack corps. {/Lieutenant Kuno ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.12,0:09:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's what you actually came for? {hope he means this: what now, turns out you brought it with you? / 貴様は持ってきていたのか}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.12,0:10:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I could only tell you how I truly feel about it \Nbecause I made up my mind already.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.12,0:10:07.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You rascal! Even tricked me into speaking my mind!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.81,0:10:26.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So how is it? How many applicants did we get?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.83,0:10:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Every single one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.17,0:10:38.60,Top,,0,0,0,,The young and hot-blooded Yokaren trainees {full meaning of yokaren is Naval Aviator Preparatory Course Trainee so I decided to leave it as is} {若い血潮の 予科練の}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.60,0:10:46.82,Top,,0,0,0,,The seven buttons anchor the cherry blossoms in our chests {七つボタンは 桜に錨}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.82,0:10:54.94,Top,,0,0,0,,We fly forth today as well, to Lake Kasumigaura... {今日も飛ぶ飛ぶ 霞ヶ浦にゃ}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.67,0:10:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Lieutenant Seki came to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.17,0:10:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.09,0:10:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey. Have a seat now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.15,0:10:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll have one, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.97,0:11:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, when our special attack corps is formed, \Nit'll be the first one of the kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.79,0:11:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So choosing a leader \Nfor such an unprecedented unit is especially difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.46,0:11:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I consulted with various staff members...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.12,0:11:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you say? \NWill you accept this position?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.11,0:11:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd be honored to. {act. "please let me do it"}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.52,0:11:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. So you will accept it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.63,0:11:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We judged that a military academy graduate \Nshould be the first to take the reins. {lit: in the beginning, ... should assume command}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.20,0:11:35.65,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, it's a matter of commanding the front line troops. \NWe're counting on you, Lieutenant Seki.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.40,0:11:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,4 vehicles from the special attack corps, \Nnewly formed on Mabalacat air base in the Philippines, {from wiki: On October 20, 1944, the First Air Fleet formed the first kamikaze special attack force . Seki was appointed as the overall commander.\N\NKuno met up with Major Tadashi Nakajima , the 201st flight commander, at the Mabalacat base, who had been instructed to form a special attack unit on Cebu Island . [5] They departed from Mabalacat and headed for Cebu Island in a total of eight Zeros, including four members of the Yamato unit, a kamikaze special attack group who had already volunteered for the suicide attack. Nakajima landed at the airfield and ordered all the crew members and mechanics to gather, and a ``Kamikaze special attack unit'' was formed, which was a surefire ramming unit, and was named Shikishima unit, Yamato unit, Asahi unit, and Yamazakura unit. He explained that the four people he had brought with him were volunteers and said, ``I have been ordered to form a special attack unit at the Cebu base. Volunteer crew members should write their name and rank, put it in a sealed envelope, and give it to the senior crew member. Please send it to me through ``I believe that some people may not be able to apply due to family circumstances.The number of flights is small, so if you are unable to apply, please honestly write a blank sheet.I will not disclose this content to anyone.}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.35,0:11:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,escorted by 4 fighters from the interception squadron \Non the 20th of October at 5 p.m. {直掩機 literally means "direct cover plane" and there's no direct translation it seems, but the description says "a patrol aircraft that orbits above the airbase/carrier it's supposed to protect to fend off any attacking aircraft" so I think interception fits; then again, these units were attached to kamikaze planes so as to provide air coverage and observe the results of a suicide attack so idk, maybe "direct support" still works better}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.42,0:11:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,were reassigned to the base on Cebu Island as part of the 201st Air Squadron under Wing Commander Nakajima, {https://ja.wikipedia.org/wiki/%E4%B8%AD%E5%B3%B6%E6%AD%A3 / https://ja.wikipedia.org/wiki/%E7%AC%AC%E4%BA%8C%E3%80%87%E4%B8%80%E6%B5%B7%E8%BB%8D%E8%88%AA%E7%A9%BA%E9%9A%8A ; no clue what they mean by "were dragged into/pulled into wing commander nakajima"; also it probably wasn't part of the 201st but w/e, I couldn't build a coherent sentence otherwise; マニラより基地に帰ってきた二丸一空飛行長中島少佐に引き入られて瀬戸を基地に転出した}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.29,0:11:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,who just returned to the base from Manila.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.59,0:12:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,In view of the current war situation, {fyi, historically they're still in Mabalacat rn}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.81,0:12:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,we decided to form a special ramming corps \Nof 26 carrier-based fighters within the 201st Air Squadron.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.11,0:12:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It will be christened \N"Special Kamikaze Attack Corps." {/divine wind}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.60,0:12:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,This attack corps will be subdivided into four units: \NShikishima, Yamato, Asahi, and Yamazakura.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.12,0:12:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Its commanding officer is Navy Lieutenant Seki Yukio.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.21,0:12:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The mission of this attack corps \Nwill be to devastate the enemy surface fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.83,0:12:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We hope to see some favorable results \Nbefore the planned engagement in the Leyte Gulf. {"results are surface fleet's rush into Leyte this is our hope" - they know about the landings so they mean "soften up the enemy before our fleets make it to leyte"}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.24,0:12:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The Yamato Unit will transfer to Cebu Base on October 20th, \Nso as to put the tactics into practice from Cebu.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.18,0:13:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,That's quite impressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.99,0:13:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you graduate from a music school, \NFirst Lieutenant Kuno?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.82,0:13:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,No, sir. My big sister was learning to play \Nand I was simply imitating her.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.10,0:13:32.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I should be ashamed. {/I'm sorry}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.49,0:13:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's nothing to be ashamed of. {lit: don't apologize}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.64,0:13:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,An important connection between music and piloting has even been proven scientifically. {/medically}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.48,0:13:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not uncommon for the fighter pilots \Nto also be piano prodigies.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.87,0:13:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Wing Commander,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.28,0:13:46.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to ask for a favor.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.18,0:13:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it, Ensign Uemura?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.20,0:13:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not getting excluded \Nfrom the Special Attack Corps, am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.18,0:13:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean by that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.50,0:13:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.18,0:13:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a recent academy graduate \Nstill mentored by First Lieutenant Kuno. {lit: I'm ...'s kohai and come from preparatory school students - no clue what he means and why he still needs someone to be his sempai so added recent; here's what I found in wiki: Nakajima entered the operation room and bedroom on the second floor after soliciting suicide mission volunteers, but Kuno immediately followed Nakajima, knocked on the door of the operation room, and as soon as he entered the room, told Nakajima, ``I'm... You won't be excluded from the Special Attack Force, right?'' he asked. Nakajima was well aware of Kuno's quiet nature, but he had something fierce in his heart, and was sure he would volunteer, so he answered, ``The special attack plane you'll be riding in was brought over from Mabalakat.'' Kunou smiled, saluted, and left the operations room }
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.71,0:14:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have a lot of flight hours so I was worried \Nabout getting excluded from regular missions. {nc why he adds every day, no idea where it belongs, added regular to substitute}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.84,0:14:05.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Marines and students \Ndon't get selected for the suicide corps. {may also mean "sailor", both don't make sense since neither is supposed to learn how to fly a plane}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.87,0:14:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're here, you have enough flight hours. \NYou've nothing to worry about.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.68,0:14:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Play us another tune.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.36,0:14:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.59,0:14:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Enemy task force of 6 aircraft carriers is located \Nabout 60 nautical miles east of Suluan Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.48,0:14:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.07,0:14:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,3 kamikaze planes, 2 interceptors. Suicide squad commander is First Lieutenant Kuno. Prepare to sortie at once! {again, maybe ki is units after all, just 3 planes are kinda useless}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.97,0:15:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Grummans are here! {HA's, can do just "we're under attack/raid"; wiki: Nakajima panicked, thinking that it was dangerous to have so many bomb-loaded Zeros lined up on the runway, but since the meeting and warnings had not yet been completed, he completed the task at a short notice, and when it was time to sortie, Kuno and his crew boarded the aircraft. Just as they were about to board the ship, American carrier-based aircraft attacked .}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.22,0:15:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Remove ordnance from kamikaze planes! \NDisperse the vehicles! {believing HA since the only word I hear here is "bomb" and the rest is a mystery; nothing in whisper either}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.25,0:15:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Start up!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.00,0:15:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Start up! {still believing HA, still no clue what it actually is}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.25,0:16:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Prepare to take off! {guess, kinda hear tobi ki yoi}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.80,0:16:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Start up the kamikaze planes! {/prepare for takeoff}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.17,0:16:16.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Pursue the enemy, don't let them slip!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.75,0:16:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Chase the enemy planes at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.18,0:16:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Find their mother ship!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.25,0:16:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Yamato Unit of the Special Kamikaze Corps takes off!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.40,0:16:33.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus, the Special Kamikaze Corps \Nwent out on its first sortie.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.05,0:16:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,However, hampered on the way by the bad weather, \N2 planes had to return unable to find the enemy. {wiki: On the way, the attack force was hindered by the weather, and the special attack Otsubo plane and the escort plane returned to Cebu Island, but the commander, Kunou, did not return and went missing. Although there was no telephone call informing him of the attack, Nakajima had sworn that he would head to Leyte before the sortie, so it was assumed that he had headed straight for Leyte Bay. It is estimated that it is able to carry out a ramming attack in search of an enemy to defeat . ' '[15] Because of Kuno's non-return, an unconfirmed claim emerged after the war that the ``first tokko attack'' was not Seki, but Yoshitaka Kuno. }
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.55,0:16:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Only the First Lieutenant Kuno's plane never returned.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.50,0:16:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Did he feel too guilty for not finding the enemy,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.75,0:16:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,or did he do it as a silent protest to the ramming attack, \Nunprecedented in history?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.80,0:16:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,In any case, First Lieutenant Kuno never returned.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.75,0:17:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And so the IJN never revealed to the public that he was in fact the first ever pilot to carry out a kamikaze mission. {/sortie on ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.14,0:17:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Was it because they failed \Nto produce any spectacular results?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.97,0:17:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Or perhaps because First Lieutenant Kuno \Nwas fresh out of the academy? {wiki: Furthermore, in response to the opinion that since Kuno was a preparatory student, the treatment was to neglect preparatory students and place more emphasis on the Marine Academy, he said}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.22,0:17:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The reasons for that \Nare shrouded in mystery even to this day.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.32,0:17:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Transmission from Shikishima Unit.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.77,0:17:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Enemy task force still not found.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.22,0:17:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Running short on fuel, \Nbut will continue the search. {nc whats zansho}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.01,0:17:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The weather seems to be bad today as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.08,0:17:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Only 3 more days until Kurita's fleet reaches Leyte.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.06,0:17:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,If we don't find and hit the enemy carrier \Nwithin the next 3 days, this strategy will be a failure. {meaning "the plan to organize kamikaze units"}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.26,0:17:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Seki also took it to heart. \NHe's desperately looking for them every day. {first half is likely 身にもなってやれ but idk what it means}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.85,0:17:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The Shikishima Unit that sortied from the Mabalacat Base
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.32,0:17:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,was spending days in the air, searching for the American task force, \Nbut still never managed to locate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.86,0:17:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,They couldn't help but to double back empty-handed. {nc whats last word}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.85,0:18:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We couldn't find them today either.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.20,0:18:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We're deeply sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.37,0:18:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you be alright? {/can your body handle it}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.53,0:18:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,First Lieutenant Kuno, \NI'm going your way too. Just you wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.99,0:18:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,26th, 0600.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.97,0:18:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The first attack corps sighted an enemy task force \Noff the coast of Suluan Island and immediately engaged.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.12,0:18:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Kamikaze unit, prepare to sortie! {nc whats first word}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.93,0:18:44.75,Default,,0,0,0,,On behalf of 100 million of our people, \NI'm praying for your success today,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.08,0:18:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Shikishima Unit of the Kamikaze Corps takes off!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.64,0:19:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,On October 25th, at 7:25 a.m.,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.55,0:19:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the Kamikaze Corps with its commander, Navy Lieutenant Seki in the lead, took off from the Mabalacat Base.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.63,0:19:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Even before the Shikishima Unit, \Nat 6:30 a.m. on the 25th,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.81,0:19:28.81,Default,,0,0,0,,6 planes from the Asahi and Yamazakura Units \Ntook off from Davao Base in Mindanao.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.09,0:19:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Motoko. Motoko, you used to laugh a lot \Nwhen you looked at my face. {motoko is his daughter fyi, not wife}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.65,0:19:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You used to sleep soundly in my embrace.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.61,0:19:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes, I'd even bathe you myself.{私の腕の中で眠りもしたしまたお風呂に入れたこともありました - unsure what last part means}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.96,0:19:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,When you grow up and start wondering about me,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.30,0:19:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,ask your mother and your aunt Kayo \Nto tell you everything about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.34,0:20:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to see it myself, \Nas you grow up and find happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.63,0:20:11.41,Default,,0,0,0,,But knowing that I die while I'm still a stranger to you, \NI won't feel any sadness. {/before you got to know me}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.41,0:20:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,When you grow up and want to see your father, \Ncome to Yasukuni Shrine. {originally "kudan" which is a district of tokyo where https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yasukuni_Shrine is located }
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.36,0:20:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,There, if you pray earnestly enough in your heart, \Nyour father's face will definitely appear before you. {/come to your mind}{this is all text from his last will: https://detail.chiebukuro.yahoo.co.jp/qa/question_detail/q1468213254}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.55,0:20:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I will always be near, watching over you. {父は常に素子の身辺を守っております。 - lit: protect one's person; around one's person}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.11,0:20:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You should become a kind person, loved by others. {人に可愛がられるやさしい人になって下さい。}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.93,0:20:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,When you grow up and start wondering about me, \Nplease ask them to read this letter to you. {お前が大きくなって私の事を考え始めた時に、この便りを読んで貰いなさい。}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.75,0:20:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,To Uemura Motoko. From father. {植村素子へ}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.56,0:20:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Transmission from the Shikishima Unit.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.07,0:21:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,1010: in the sea east of Samar Island, 4 to 5 battleships, \Nplus over 30 cruisers, destroyers, and other vessels. {nc what's suguta}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.96,0:21:05.09,Default,,0,0,0,,In the air above them, \Nspotted over 20 Grummans heading north. {HA's, nc whats zaiku and all around it; makes me wonder where did grummans came from if he didn't name any carriers}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.35,0:21:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Shikishima Unit reporting. 1040. Located one formation about 90 nautical miles from Tacloban, at 85 degrees.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.93,0:21:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,4 carriers, 6 cruisers and destroyers. \NProceeding to strike immediately!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.60,0:21:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Plane 1, commence attack. {probably an order, but maybe he reports the results; assuming it's an order, he actually says something like "proceed to ram them"}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.87,0:22:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Plane 2, commence attack. \NPlane 3 follow suit! {guess, kinda hear "mo" there}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.29,0:23:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus, the Special Kamikaze Attack Corps was born.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.40,0:23:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And until the end of the war, more than 2,500 \Nyoung bright lives would be wasted one after another. {nc what's yuuyomei and chitte, was "scattered" in HA}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.13,0:23:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I speak to the souls of the fallen kamikaze. \NI bow and thank you for your spirited fight. {another excerpt from takijiro onishi's last will: https://www.royallibrary.sakura.ne.jp/ww2/text/oonishi_isho.html}{「特攻隊の英霊に申す。善く戦いたり、感謝す。 }
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.01,0:23:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You believed in our ultimate victory, \Nand scattered your lives like petals in suicide attacks. {最後の勝利を信じつつ肉弾として散華せり。- /met your heroic end}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.60,0:23:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Even so, we found ourselves being unable \Nto live up to that conviction of yours. {然れどもその信念は遂に達成し得ざるに至れり。}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.73,0:23:42.27,Default,,0,0,0,,With my death, I would like to apologize to the heroic spirits of my former subordinates and their families. {吾死を以て旧部下の英霊とその遣族に謝せんとす。}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.61,0:23:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Those passing their judgment upon others \Nhave to be prepared to be judged themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.38,0:23:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Even knowing their sentence shall be that of death. {guess, lit is kinda "say, even if it's in death", maybe means "even if it means they'll die" or maybe "after they die [in purgatory etc]"}
